<worksheet >
    <title>FUN-1 Vector Operations and Applications</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>To earn an M on this outcome, you will need to correctly complete both problems. To earn a P on this outcome, you will need to correctly complete 
        problem 2 and one part of problem 1.</p>
  </introduction>  
  <page>
    <exercise workspace="1.5in">
        <introduction><p>Let <m>\vec{u}=\langle 4,1,-2\rangle, \vec{v}=\langle 2,-2,1\rangle,</m> 
            and <m>\vec{w}=\langle 0,3,1\rangle</m></p></introduction>
      <task><statement><p>Find <m>\vec{v}\cdot(\vec{u}\times\vec{w})</m></p></statement></task>
      <task><statement><p>Find the vector in the direction of <m>\vec{w}</m> with length of 
        <m>3\vec{v}</m>.</p></statement></task>
    </exercise>
    <exercise workspace="1.5in">
      <statement><p>A flat solar panel is defined by a directed area normal vector 
        <m>\vec{A} = \langle 2, 4, 5\rangle{m}^{2}</m>. A constant solar radiation 
        flow field passes through it, given by the vector field <m>\vec{F} = \langle 10, -2, 6\rangle</m> units. 
        Find the total solar energy flux passing through the panel using the dot product.</p></statement>
    </exercise>
  </page>
</worksheet>